    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Brice Turang** (75.06) headline the lineup as our primary point-producers. **Mickey Moniak** is in a prime spot against the 5.19 xERA of Buehler; his ability to exploit the pitcher's slow delivery provides a quantifiable boost to our scarcest category, stolen bases. Similarly, **Brice Turang** earns a strong endorsement batting lead-off against Irvin; the high-upside order spot paired with the favorable SP matchup gives him the highest ceiling of the day. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.92) also grades out as a elite-tier start, though his outlook is tempered by a 31% rain risk that necessitates monitoring as the game approaches.\n\nThe decision-making process for the utility slots was particularly tight, with **Josh Naylor** (64.69) and **Tyler Soderstrom** (63.69) securing starts over several high-profile bench options. **Alex Freeland** (50.90) came closest to cracking the starting nine, but his bottom-of-the-order placement and lower baseline projection relegated him to the bench in favor of **Tyler Soderstrom**, who benefits from the premium #4 lineup spot. Meanwhile, we are proceeding with caution regarding **Gabriel Moreno**, whose score of 46.93 sits at the bottom of our starters due to a difficult matchup against Luzardo. While we are keeping **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (47.75) and **Giancarlo Stanton** (47.67) on the bench today due to unfavorable platoon splits against Matz, they remain on high alert should any late-inning tactical shifts occur. We are currently comfortable with **Max Muncy** (51.78) and **James Wood** (50.18) filling out the bottom of the roster, noting that while **James Wood** faces a tough arm in Ashby, his lead-off role and stolen base potential keep him in the mix for daily efficiency.",
